es in this life.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;As you do sadhana,=\r\n try not to fancy too many specific\n&gt;  desires. Nature has a delay mechanis=\r\nm in granting your desires (because of constraints on what Nature can give =\r\nyou right now, arising from YOUR\n&gt;  OWN previous actions). So Nature someti=\r\nmes gives you what you want LATE, when you no longer want it or want someth=\r\ning else. For example, one may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and b=\r\ne born as a rich but very sick man in next life. One may not enjoy that wea=\r\nlth and pray whole life for health. In the life after that, one may be very=\r\n healthy, but not have any knowledge or money. In another \n&gt; case, one may =\r\ndeeply desire to act in a famous film. One may be reborn \n&gt; as a tiger or a=\r\n dog and act in a famous film, but not really enjoy that \n&gt; experience. Bas=\r\nically, people keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking=\r\n&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kunda=\r\nlini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience given by a rising Kun=\r\ndalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having it in THIS life,=\r\n one may be born in next life with this specific desire destined to fructif=\r\ny (if there is enough karmik force behind it).\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0\n=\r\n&gt;  *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful, if =\r\none is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;On=\r\nce I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to free it and it panicke=\r\nd so badly and started to shake violently. I went to save it from a certain=\r\n slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;We are l=\r\nike that chipmunk, glued to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex an=\r\nd scared of being rescued from a certain slow death!\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;If our =\r\nideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are incorrect a=\r\nnd if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete realiza=\r\ntion of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-mind complex, =\r\nwithout being scared?\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundali=\r\nni rise after most undesirable conditioning is overcome, is far better than=\r\n\n&gt;  Kundalini rise forced when some really undesirable conditioning is stil=\r\nl left in one&#39;s system.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends one problematic =\r\nnotion about who one is and what one needs, another notion that lay buried =\r\ndeeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one. If one o=\r\nvercomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion in one&#39;s b=\r\nody-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (e.g. a great doctor, a =\r\ngreat leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme example, i=\r\nf one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescues the wo=\r\nrld, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescue the wor=\r\nld now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any su=\r\nch notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some signs of progress a=\r\nnd yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;An awakened =\r\nKundalini in a system with undesirable conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s we=\r\naknesses and wrong notions heavily and cause serious psychiatric and spirit=\r\nual problems.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;The best approa=\r\nch I recommend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do =\r\nsadhana, overcome your\n&gt;  weaknesses and improve your detachment over time.=\r\n Again, I want to emphasize that detachment is not disgust or distaste for =\r\nlife/things/people around you. Disgust is the other side of coin of attachm=\r\nent. It is a negative attachment.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about \n&gt; =\r\nwhether your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether you are able to re=\r\nsist 6 internal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) or \n&gt; not=\r\n. If your ability to resist them is increasing, you are making progress. EV=\r\nEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still making progress. When yo=\r\nu completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) \n&gt; will automat=\r\nically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self).\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal deity. Th=\r\nough true surrender is helpful, most people do not have it. They simply do =\r\nbusiness with god. Though people may be offended by my words, this is the p=\r\nlain and bare fact.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&quot;I want X, I will pray to you and please=\r\n give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini rise, I will pray to you and ple=\r\nase protect me&quot; - all this is just a business deal. There is something you =\r\nwant and you ask god for it. True surrender has no place for agendas, desir=\r\nes, demands or expectations. True surrender is losing oneself in one&#39;s fasc=\r\nination for the qualities of Lord. True surrender is accepting anything Lor=\r\nd throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or highly painful) as Lord&#39;s =\r\nprasad and accepting it gratefully. True surrender is thinking of Lord with=\r\n fascination and pleasure, even in the face of (and during) Death.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;If one without true surrender and with many desires and wrong notio=\r\nns experiences a Kundalini rise, one may still be trapped, despite thinking=\r\n of a personal god. It is not that god does not want to &quot;protect&quot; one as sa=\r\nid below. It is not about protecting or endangering. If you go back to my &quot;=\r\nchipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was trying to protect it, bu=\r\nt it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning makes one *run away* from Go=\r\nd&#39;s\n&gt;  protection! God&#39;s protection may seem to a conditioned mind like gra=\r\nve danger that one should run away from!\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=\r\n=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether through the path of wisdom or surrender, develop dispass=\r\nion and detachment. Realize that all this is temporary and can be taken awa=\r\ny anytime. Enjoy it while you have and keep doing your best, but be prepare=\r\nd to lose everything anytime. Only detachment and a very light mental condi=\r\ntioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can protect one as one&#39;s Kundali=\r\nni rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and impurities in one&#39;s nadi=\r\ns will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) and stop Her from meeting=\r\n True Self.\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;The real key is how light your conditioning is.\n=\r\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Best regards,\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Narasimha\n&gt; &gt;&gt;--------\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Astrology & Spi=\r\nrituality Resources: http://www.VedicAstrologer.org\n&gt; &gt;&gt;--------\n&gt; &gt;&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n=C2=A0\n&gt; &gt;&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;________________________________\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt; From: Leela Sa=\r