ot to fancy too many specific&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n  desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desires (because o=\r\nf constraints on what Nature can give you right now, arising from YOUR&lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt;  OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want LA=\r\nTE, when you no longer want it or want something else. For example, one may=\r\n pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very sick=\r\n man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for he=\r\nalth. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, but not have any kno=\r\nwledge or money. In another &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; case, one may deeply desire to act in=\r\n a famous film. One may be reborn &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; as a tiger or a dog and act in =\r\na famous film, but not really enjoy that &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; experience. Basically, p=\r\neople keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; somethi=\r\nng they are &quot;missing&quot;.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, com=\r\ning back to Kundalini, if one deeply desires an out of body experience give=\r\nn by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from having=\r\n it in THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desire de=\r\nstined to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &g=\r\nt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nb=\r\nsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful, if=\r\n one is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt=\r\n;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I wen=\r\nt to free it and it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I wen=\r\nt to save it from a certain slow death and it was scared that I would kill =\r\nit!&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glu=\r\ned to the mouse trap called this body-mind complex and scared of being resc=\r\nued from a certain slow death!&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;If =\r\nour ideas about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are incorre=\r\nct and if we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete rea=\r\nlization of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-mind compl=\r\nex, without being scared?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after most u=\r\nndesirable conditioning is overcome, is far better than&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  Kundalini=\r\n rise forced when some really undesirable conditioning is still left in one=\r\n&#39;s system.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends one=\r\n problematic notion about who one is and what one needs, another notion tha=\r\nt lay buried deeper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment =\r\none. If one overcomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another noti=\r\non in one&#39;s body-mind complex that one&#39;s awareness clings on to (e.g. a gre=\r\nat doctor, a great leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extre=\r\nme example, if one person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who r=\r\nescues the world, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will r=\r\nescue the world now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply cli=\r\nngs to any such notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some signs =\r\nof progress and yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&=\r\ngt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;An awakened Kundalini in a system with undesirab=\r\nle conditioning may accentuate one&#39;s weaknesses and wrong notions heavily a=\r\nnd cause serious psychiatric and spiritual problems.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\nThe best approach I recommend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini and its=\r\n rise. Just do sadhana, overcome your&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  weaknesses and improve your=\r\n detachment over time. Again, I want to emphasize that detachment is not di=\r\nsgust or distaste for life/things/people around you. Disgust is the other s=\r\nide of coin of attachment. It is a negative attachment.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&n=\r\nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; whether=\r\n your Kundalini rises or not. Worry about whether you are able to resist 6 =\r\ninternal enemies (shadripus) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) or &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; not=\r\n. If your ability to resist them is increasing, you are making progress. EV=\r\nEN IF your Kundalini is fast asleep, you are still making progress. When yo=\r\nu completely overcome them, Kundalini (your self-awareness) &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; will =\r\nautomatically ascend to the top and meet Her Lord (true Self).&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt=\r\n;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt=\r\n; &gt;&gt;One word on surrendering to a personal deity. Though true surrend=\r\ner is helpful, most people do not have it. They simply do business with god=\r\n. Though people may be offended by my words, this is the plain and bare fac=\r\nt.&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&quot;I want X, I will pray to you a=\r\nnd please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am scared of Kundalini rise, I will pray to yo=\r\nu and please protect me&quot; - all this is just a business deal. There is somet=\r\nhing you want and you ask god for it. True surrender has no place for agend=\r\nas, desires, demands or expectations. True surrender is losing oneself in o=\r\nne&#39;s fascination for the qualities of Lord. True surrender is accepting any=\r\nthing Lord throws one&#39;s way (whether it is pleasurable or highly painful) a=\r\ns Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it gratefully. True surrender is thinking of =\r\nLord with fascination and pleasure, even in the face of (and during) Death.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;If one without true surrender and=\r\n with many desires and wrong notions experiences a Kundalini rise, one may =\r\nstill be trapped, despite thinking of a personal god. It is not that god do=\r\nes not want to &quot;protect&quot; one as said below. It is not about protecting or e=\r\nndangering. If you go back to my &quot;chipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example abo=\r\nve, I was trying to protect it, but it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditi=\r\noning makes one *run away* from God&#39;s&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;  protection! God&#39;s protectio=\r\nn may seem to a conditioned mind like grave danger that one should run away=\r\n from!&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt=\r\n;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether through the path of wisdom or surrende=\r\nr, develop dispassion and detachment. Realize that all this is temporary an=\r\nd can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it while you have and keep doing your be=\r\nst, but be prepared to lose everything anytime. Only detachment and a very =\r\nlight mental conditioning (very light desires, dislikes etc) can protect on=\r\ne as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True Self. Heavy conditioning and impuri=\r\nties in one&#39;s nadis will distract rising Kundalini (self-awareness) and sto=\r\np Her from m